    Element
    Description
    org.eclipse.pde.core.IModelProviderEvent.ENVIRONMENT_CHANGED
    Since the 4.4 Luna release, target platform changes are not tracked as model events
    org.eclipse.pde.core.IModelProviderEvent.TARGET_CHANGED
    Since the 4.4 Luna release, target platform changes are not tracked as model events
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(String, String, int, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    If no filter is passed use PluginRegistry.findModel(String, String, VersionMatchRule), else filter the Stream returned by PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, VersionMatchRule).
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(String, VersionRange, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    If no filter is passed use PluginRegistry.findModel(String, VersionRange), else filter the Stream returned by PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange).
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(BundleDescription)
    Instead use PluginRegistry.findModel(Resource)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, int, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    Instead use PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, VersionMatchRule) and filter the returned Stream if a filter is passed.
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    Instead use PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange) and filter the returned Stream if a filter is passed.
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.PluginFilter
    Instead use Predicate and filter the stream returned by PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, VersionMatchRule) or PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.project.IBundleProjectService.newHost(String, VersionRange)
    Instead use IBundleProjectService.newHost(String, VersionRange)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.project.IBundleProjectService.newPackageImport(String, VersionRange, boolean)
    Instead use IBundleProjectService.newPackageImport(String, VersionRange, boolean)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.project.IBundleProjectService.newRequiredBundle(String, VersionRange, boolean, boolean)
    Instead use IBundleProjectService.newRequiredBundle(String, VersionRange, boolean, boolean)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.project.IHostDescription.getVersionRange()
    Instead use IHostDescription.version()
    org.eclipse.pde.core.project.IPackageImportDescription.getVersionRange()
    Instead use IPackageImportDescription.version()

    Instead use IRequiredBundleDescription.version()

    not used anymore

  • Deprecated Methods
    Method
    Description
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.IPluginModelBase.getBuildModel()
    This method has always returned null. Since 3.7, use PluginRegistry.createBuildModel(IPluginModelBase) instead.
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.IPluginModelBase.getNLLookupLocation()
    The URL returned is not encoded. If the file path contains special characters such as # this URL cannot be used for opening streams. Instead use ISharedPluginModel.getInstallLocation() and create the URL using an encoding tool such as URIUtil. Deprecated in 4.3.
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(String, String, int, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    If no filter is passed use PluginRegistry.findModel(String, String, VersionMatchRule), else filter the Stream returned by PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, VersionMatchRule).
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(String, VersionRange, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    If no filter is passed use PluginRegistry.findModel(String, VersionRange), else filter the Stream returned by PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange).
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModel(BundleDescription)
    Instead use PluginRegistry.findModel(Resource)
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, int, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
    Instead use PluginRegistry.findModels(String, String, VersionMatchRule) and filter the returned Stream if a filter is passed.
    org.eclipse.pde.core.plugin.PluginRegistry.findModels(String, VersionRange, PluginRegistry.PluginFilter)
